<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="164" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="3.[172,1379,284,595]" pageId="3" pageNumber="164">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[174,521,284,317]" pageId="3" pageNumber="164">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Classified as Least Concern on The IUCN Red List. The Greater Hedgehog 
<taxonomicName box="[368,465,323,356]" class="Mammalia" family="Tenrecidae" genus="Tenrec" kingdom="Animalia" order="Afrosoricida" pageId="3" pageNumber="164" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Tenrec</taxonomicName>
is widespread, has a stable overall population, and occurs in various primary and disturbed habitats. Although it can be locally threatened by overhunting and habitat loss, it does not face any 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Major" baseAuthorityYear="1896" box="[744,827,402,435]" class="Mammalia" family="Tenrecidae" genus="Microgale" kingdom="Animalia" order="Afrosoricida" pageId="3" pageNumber="164" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="major">major</taxonomicName>
conservation threats.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
